text.tspan: Detecting PTMs in Cryo-EM Density Maps with MS² Data
Dari Kimanius, Mounika Challoori, Leonie von Berlin & Revant Gupta

flowRoot.flowPara: Cryogenic electron microscopy (Cryo-EM) has enabled new insights into structural properties of large biomolecules. But despite recent development in resolution identifying post-translational modifications (PTMs) in Cryo-EM density maps is still a challenging task. As PTMs play an important role in structural and functional properties of proteins, new strategies for their identification would be of great value. Here we demonstrate how the combination of MS² data analysis and Cryo-EM density maps can lead to the detection of new, potential PTMs in the large subunit of the human mitochondrial ribosome.
